LudoTrace is a session journal for Stardew Valley. Every time you sleep, it writes an impartial record of your day to a plain JSONL file — monsters killed, fish caught, gifts given, quests started, friendship changes, what you shipped, and how you spent your energy. No overlays, no opinions, no configuration. Just the data.

What you do with it is up to you. Paste it into an AI for coaching, comedy reacts, or a stat breakdown. Feed it into your own tools. An example AI prompt is included.

No configuration required. File-drop install — works with any Stardew Valley save.

[size=5][b]What it logs[/b][/size]

Every session captures:

[list]
[*]Character snapshot at start and end — money, energy, skill levels, relationship hearts[/*]
[*]Locations visited (deduped — each location logged once per session)[/*]
[*]Monsters killed — name and in-game time[/*]
[*]Fish caught — species, size (inches), location[/*]
[*]Gifts given — NPC, item, reaction (loved / liked / neutral / disliked / hated)[/*]
[*]Sleep result — slept normally vs passed out from exhaustion[/*]
[*]Quest changes — started and completed during the day[/*]
[*]Skill level-ups — farming, mining, foraging, fishing, combat[/*]
[*]Items consumed — food and consumables with category[/*]
[*]Friendship changes — per NPC, per day, in friendship points[/*]
[*]Crops shipped — item, count, gold value[/*]
[*]Recipes learned — cooking and crafting[/*]
[*]Mine floor reached — with Skull Cavern flag[/*]
[*]Golden Walnut zone visits (Ginger Island)[/*]
[/list]

The log is plain JSONL (one JSON object per line) written to:

[code]Stardew Valley\lt_stardew_events.jsonl[/code]

Example:

[code]{"type":"session_start","game_date":"spring 15 Y1","game_time":"06:00","farmer_name":"Kris","money":4200,"energy":270,"skills":{"farming":1,"mining":0,"foraging":1,"fishing":2,"combat":0},"relationships":[{"npc":"Penny","hearts":0},{"npc":"Sam","hearts":1},{"npc":"Leah","hearts":2}]}
{"type":"location","name":"Town","game_date":"spring 15 Y1","game_time":"08:30"}
{"type":"gift","npc":"Penny","item":"Parsnip","reaction":"disliked","game_date":"spring 15 Y1","game_time":"09:10"}
{"type":"location","name":"Forest","game_date":"spring 15 Y1","game_time":"10:00"}
{"type":"fish","name":"Catfish","size":22,"location":"Forest","game_date":"spring 15 Y1","game_time":"11:40"}
{"type":"used","item":"Salmonberry","category":"food","game_date":"spring 15 Y1","game_time":"13:20"}
{"type":"sleep","result":"slept","game_date":"spring 15 Y1"}
{"type":"quest_stage","quest":"Delivery: Penny","stage":"started","game_date":"spring 15 Y1"}
{"type":"friendship","npc":"Penny","hearts":0,"delta":-50,"game_date":"spring 15 Y1"}
{"type":"session_end","game_date":"spring 16 Y1","game_time":"06:00","farmer_name":"Kris","money":4200,"energy":270,"skills":{"farming":1,"mining":0,"foraging":1,"fishing":2,"combat":0}}[/code]

You can read it, parse it, or feed it into any tool you like. The Claude.ai coaching workflow is built in, but the log is yours.

[size=5][b]The coaching workflow[/b][/size]

[b]1. Play.[/b] Load any save — SMAPI registers the mod automatically on load. Sleep to end the day and flush that session's events.

[b]2. Open Claude.ai.[/b] Start a new chat at claude.ai (free account works fine).

[b]3. Paste the prompt + your log.[/b] A coaching prompt is included as [font=Courier New]coaching_prompt.md[/font] in the zip. Paste it, then paste the contents of [font=Courier New]lt_stardew_events.jsonl[/font] below it.

[b]4. Get coaching.[/b] Claude reads your session and gives you specific, actionable feedback based on what actually happened — not generic Stardew tips.

[size=5][b]Example output when piped through Claude[/b][/size]

[i](From a real session — Year 1 Spring 15)[/i]

[quote]You caught a 22-inch Catfish and left the river before noon. Catfish only appear after 6PM in rainy weather — check tomorrow's forecast. A rainy Spring 16 is your best shot before the season ends.

Penny received a Parsnip and lost 50 friendship points. She loves Melons and Poppies — neither is hard to grow in Summer. Her birthday is Summer 2, which is your first gift window of the season. A loved birthday gift gives 8× the normal friendship points.

Spring 15 with 4,200g and zero crops shipped. Pierre still has Bean Starters at 60g each. They can be planted through Spring 18 and return in 10 days — that's still a profitable spring window if you plant today.[/quote]

The coaching references your actual session — your fish, your gifts, your money — not a wiki guide.

[size=5][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://smapi.io/]SMAPI 4.0 or later[/url][/*]
[/list]

[size=5][b]Install[/b][/size]

Drop the [font=Courier New]LudoTrace[/font] folder from the zip into your [font=Courier New]Stardew Valley\Mods\[/font] directory. SMAPI will load it automatically on next launch.

Or install via Vortex — the zip is structured correctly for auto-deployment.

